item.title: I love musicals now and hate this cunt
item.content:encoded:
Good morning i guess or whatever i dunno its another one of these! Last time i did end up doing edits but they were for the better so now i must admit that editing your writing is actually good?? Bananas i know.

Anyway onto the thing

Photo Life Updates

I found my old house captain badge from primary school and still remember being egged on to put my name down by the teachers (after i refused to do prefect or captain) and then later being like “can i take my name off” and the teacher was like “oh no you cant. Youre the only one left everyone else who went for house captain got either captain or prefect” and then having to do an speec which was “hi my names jack and i like sport” and then andrew (god i wish i remembered his last name, like 3 people receiving this will be the only people who know it) refused to vote for me and i legit was like “oh i might get 0 votes” but i did win and the only cool thing was i once had to run an assembly with will curuthers who was at the time a good foot and a half shorter than me and all the girls were doing a dance thing anyway this is really long jesus christ.

Maccas had a thing on for dismicible me 4 where its a banana and caramel mcflurry. Turns out its just a camarle sunday with the banana and caramel pie shoved into it. Pretty mid especially because i ate one of the pies on my drive home and then had to eat another one but with ice cream.

I made these cookies and i gotta recommend them, theyre like $10 and are slightly hard to cook but theyre so nice

Saw montainges trial show that was fun, it had some of the dopest lighting effects (like the entire show was good but even they called out how dope the lighting was)

Got a haircut and immediately felt less depressed but also like “fuck ive got a wedding in september im gonna need to get it cut again prior to that”

Realised my monitor does Picture in Picture so i can use my work laptop and my pc to play balatro at the same time

Got an aftermarket head unit for my mums car off ebay for her birthday and installed it with my brother. Well when i say with i bought it. And then held the torch. And then when the unit didnt fit because it was too big helped remove the one from his car and transplant it into hers. But it counts

Went to the reverse trash place and they had this “patch” which i had to buy for 50 cents

Got obsessed with trying to beat solitaire on my ipod, this is a photo i had to take of my best attempt

Fornite

Fuck i love this game, its dumb and bad and monitized to shit and also sometimes minotonous but also its a blast. I cant work out how to take in game screenshots so enjoy these pictures i took on my phone

I managed to get a car stuck in a hole by accident while my friend was afk

Placed 5th with 1 assist and 0% accuracy

The music mode lets you do normal emotes which is fun

Got a car stuck in a hole for a second time

I got a car in a place where it was more appropriate for people and was legit laughing at myself

Deadpool and wolverine

Ill be honest and say i read most of the rumours and leaks for this movie and went “jesus that'll be bad. But im not gonna see it” and then a friend was like “hey do you wanna go see it” and for some reason i saw it on 8:30pm on a thursday night. Right before it started i remembered how much i hate ryan reynolds as deadpool and i walked out feeling empty. Like the movie had robbed me of 2 hours and had nothing to show from it. Its now 11:51pm and im listening to music and drinking a tea to try and wind down for bed because the comic book movie was so atrocious. I liked the first dead pool movie. But also that was 2016 and i was 19. The 2nd one was in 2018 and i was 21 and found the entire thing rather grating. Now its 2024. Im 27 and im far to fucking old for a deadpool thats still trying to be like its 2016

Some good things i watched

  • I found a link (by asking someone on reddit very nicely) to an bootleg of the new merrily we roll along that just closed and its fantastic

  • Black friday (starkid) - im still not sure how i feel about the horror hatcherfield musicals starkid are doing but i enjoyed this (i think my problem is theres no clear protagonist setup early on? Like this has smoker kid and also old man but they dip in terms of who feels like the main character)

  • The fall guy - fine movie. But its filmed in sydney and therefore the chase scenes pissed me off to no end because i could tell the route they were taking and it made no sense there was just a big loop

  • Little women at hayes - i don't think i can hate anything they produce

  • Deadpool and wolverine - see above

Moving out???

So I started writing this last week and was worried there'd be nothing to talk about but I guess now I'm moving out? It's currently Monday the 29th at 1pm and I'm currently stuck in my work office having a slight panic attack. Just from sheer “wait what have I just signed up for???”

So anyway thats gonna be that

Until next month

Jack out

(im thinking of watching mordecai again which feels like a cry for help but also if anyone wants to watch it with me ewen mcgreggor truly tries to cuck his wife its hilarious)

le end
